<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;qr-code-wc&gt;</code> component generates a QR code from text or a URL. It uses progressive enhancement: the text content is visible before JavaScript loads, then replaced with a scannable QR code canvas.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/examples/demos/qr-code-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/qr-code"
      title="QR Code Demo"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Basic QR code">{{ basicCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <aside class="note">
      <strong>Zero dependencies.</strong> The QR encoder is built-in &mdash; no external library required. Supports byte mode encoding for versions 1&ndash;10.
    </aside>
  </section>

